{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01W3YzFf3RDDoKBuPTGiPiZs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’####\n     2â†’# This Dockerfile is used in order to build a container that runs the Quarkus application in JVM mode\n     3â†’#\n     4â†’# Before building the container image run:\n     5â†’#\n     6â†’# ./mvnw package -Dquarkus.package.type=fast-jar\n     7â†’#\n     8â†’# Then, build the image with:\n     9â†’#\n    10â†’# docker build -f src/main/docker/Dockerfile.fast-jar -t quarkus/quarkuscoffeeshop-majestic-monolith-fast-jar .\n    11â†’#\n    12â†’# Then run the container using:\n    13â†’#\n    14â†’# docker run -i --rm -p 8080:8080 quarkus/quarkuscoffeeshop-majestic-monolith-fast-jar\n    15â†’#\n    16â†’# If you want to include the debug port into your docker image\n    17â†’# you will have to expose the debug port (default 5005) like this :  EXPOSE 8080 5050\n    18â†’#\n    19â†’# Then run the container using :\n    20â†’#\n    21â†’# docker run -i --rm -p 8080:8080 -p 5005:5005 -e JAVA_ENABLE_DEBUG=\"true\" quarkus/quarkuscoffeeshop-majestic-monolith-fast-jar\n    22â†’#\n    23â†’###\n    24â†’FROM registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi-minimal:8.3 \n    25â†’\n    26â†’ARG JAVA_PACKAGE=java-11-openjdk-headless\n    27â†’ARG RUN_JAVA_VERSION=1.3.8\n    28â†’ENV LANG='en_US.UTF-8' LANGUAGE='en_US:en'\n    29â†’# Install java and the run-java script\n    30â†’# Also set up permissions for user `1001`\n    31â†’RUN microdnf install curl ca-certificates ${JAVA_PACKAGE} \\\n    32â†’    && microdnf update \\\n    33â†’    && microdnf clean all \\\n    34â†’    && mkdir /deployments \\\n    35â†’    && chown 1001 /deployments \\\n    36â†’    && chmod \"g+rwX\" /deployments \\\n    37â†’    && chown 1001:root /deployments \\\n    38â†’    && curl https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/fabric8/run-java-sh/${RUN_JAVA_VERSION}/run-java-sh-${RUN_JAVA_VERSION}-sh.sh -o /deployments/run-java.sh \\\n    39â†’    && chown 1001 /deployments/run-java.sh \\\n    40â†’    && chmod 540 /deployments/run-java.sh \\\n    41â†’    && echo \"securerandom.source=file:/dev/urandom\" >> /etc/alternatives/jre/lib/security/java.security\n    42â†’\n    43â†’# Configure the JAVA_OPTIONS, you can add -XshowSettings:vm to also display the heap size.\n    44â†’ENV JAVA_OPTIONS=\"-Dquarkus.http.host=0.0.0.0 -Djava.util.logging.manager=org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager\"\n    45â†’# We make four distinct layers so if there are application changes the library layers can be re-used\n    46â†’COPY --chown=1001 target/quarkus-app/lib/ /deployments/lib/\n    47â†’COPY --chown=1001 target/quarkus-app/*.jar /deployments/\n    48â†’COPY --chown=1001 target/quarkus-app/app/ /deployments/app/\n    49â†’COPY --chown=1001 target/quarkus-app/quarkus/ /deployments/quarkus/\n    50â†’\n    51â†’EXPOSE 8080\n    52â†’USER 1001\n    53â†’\n    54â†’ENTRYPOINT [ \"/deployments/run-java.sh\" ]\n    55â†’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uiq62jBtTG2cduLDeZk4rf","session_id":"55a9df99-a1b9-45b0-ac12-d337ab838722","uuid":"0f1ddd0c-8fe9-4002-918d-36a0cd4735bd"}
