{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Rm6DKeTqeLBiY7djqbGgqA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’####\n     2â†’# This Dockerfile is used in order to build a container that runs the Quarkus application in native (no JVM) mode\n     3â†’#\n     4â†’# Before building the container image run:\n     5â†’#\n     6â†’# ./mvnw package -Pnative\n     7â†’#\n     8â†’# Then, build the image with:\n     9â†’#\n    10â†’# docker build -f src/main/docker/Dockerfile.native -t quarkus/quarkuscoffeeshop-majestic-monolith .\n    11â†’#\n    12â†’# Then run the container using:\n    13â†’#\n    14â†’# docker run -i --rm -p 8080:8080 quarkus/quarkuscoffeeshop-majestic-monolith\n    15â†’#\n    16â†’###\n    17â†’FROM registry.access.redhat.com/ubi8/ubi-minimal:8.3\n    18â†’WORKDIR /work/\n    19â†’RUN chown 1001 /work \\\n    20â†’    && chmod \"g+rwX\" /work \\\n    21â†’    && chown 1001:root /work\n    22â†’COPY --chown=1001:root target/*-runner /work/application\n    23â†’\n    24â†’EXPOSE 8080\n    25â†’USER 1001\n    26â†’\n    27â†’CMD [\"./application\", \"-Dquarkus.http.host=0.0.0.0\"]\n    28â†’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Uiq62jBtTG2cduLDeZk4rf","session_id":"55a9df99-a1b9-45b0-ac12-d337ab838722","uuid":"352663b8-651c-4c42-b937-bccf2cc4e692"}
